article.headline: Montana State 71, Idaho State 54
article.story: BOZEMAN, Mont. (AP) -- Nick Dissly scored all 18 of his points in the second half to lead Montana State to a 71-54 victory Thursday over Idaho State. Dissly, who missed the only shot he took in the first half, was 5-of-6 from the field in the second and a perfect 6-of-6 from the free-throw line. After Idaho State (8-13, 2-6 Big Sky) pulled to 45-43 on a short jumper by Logan Kinghorn with 10:38 remaining, the Bobcats (11-10, 6-2 Big Sky) went on a 19-2 run and led 64-45 following Ja'Ron Jefferson's 3-pointer at the 5:15 mark. Al Beye and Jefferson each scored 12 points and Brandon Miller added 10 for the Bobcats. The Bengals' Jeff Gardner scored 10 of his team-high 13 points in the first half and Nate Rede had 11. Beye hit all five of his field goal attempts in the first half and teammate Marvin Moss was also perfect from the field in the first 20 minutes, hitting three field goals and 3-of-3 free throws. Montana State failed to hit a 3-pointer in the first half and had a difficult time hanging on to the ball. The Bobcats were 0-9 on 3-point tries and turned the ball over 14 times. They improved to 7-of-15 on 3-pointers in the second half and committed 10 turnovers. Casey Durham tied the game at 30 with three free throws after getting fouled on a 3-point try with 1.8 seconds left in the half.
